## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-102">Un `SpeechDetected` evento es desencadenado por la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> y <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> clases.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-102">A `SpeechDetected` event is raised by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-103">**SpeechDetected** se generan eventos cuando un motor de reconocimiento puede identificar la entrada de audio como voz humana.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-103">**SpeechDetected** events are generated when a recognition engine can identify audio input as human speech.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechDetectedEventArgs> se deriva de <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechDetectedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-105">El ejemplo siguiente crea un controlador para <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> eventos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-105">The example below creates a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-106">El controlador Inicializa una pantalla cada vez que se detecta y muestra información de estado, incluida la posición de audio de voz.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-106">The handler initializes a display every time speech is detected and displays status information, including audio position.</span></span>  
  
```  
_recognizer.SpeechDetected +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechDetectedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Clear previous recognition information.  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Enabled = true;  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Visible = true;  
    Utils.DisplayAudioInputFormat(_audioStateLabel, _recognizer);  
    Utils.DisplayRecognizerState(_recognizerStateLabel, _recognizer.State);  
    Utils.DisplaySpeechDetected(_speechDetectedLabel, eventArgs.AudioPosition);  
  };  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-109">El ejemplo siguiente crea un controlador para <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> eventos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-109">The example below creates a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c29b7-110">El controlador Inicializa una pantalla de voz de cada hora se detecta y muestra información de estado, incluida la posición de audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c29b7-110">The handler initializes a display each time speech is detected and displays status information, including audio position.</span></span>  
  
```  
_recognizer.SpeechDetected +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechDetectedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Clear previous recognition information.  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Enabled = true;  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Visible = true;  
    Utils.DisplayAudioInputFormat(_audioStateLabel, _recognizer);  
    Utils.DisplayRecognizerState(_recognizerStateLabel, _recognizer.State);  
    Utils.DisplaySpeechDetected(_speechDetectedLabel, eventArgs.AudioPosition);  
  };  
```
